author: @mabiegm
text:
To My Lalisa Manoban. 
It's really funny to think how I get here. I mean I admit from the very first video that I watched from YouTube it was "How You Like That" dance practice ad's on YouTube. I totally disliked you all BLACKPINK I find it nonsense to listen, watch, even support any kpop groups. I felt really weird for the fans/people who supports kpop groups. I don't like the style, it's so immature, I don't like the fashion it's so vulgar, I don't like the sound I totally don't like kpop thing before. The way this kpop groups look so stupid for me.
But, things changed. Lisa, change my perspective about it. I still don't like the culture, the vibe, the sound and all. But what I found with Lisa and Blackpink, is the.. Sound of madness with their music. I tried to listen "Stay" and the cover of "Sure Thing" but stay hits me that hard. And Lisa's rapline with whistles I don't know what change my mind. Then I started to discover, I search more about them. Most specially Lisa. And I read a lot of articles about her. And her story amazed me. Her hardship,The path she walked through and the core. Maaan this girl hits me this hard that even me didn't expected. I was the Metal core, Metal head rock person who listen Indie rock too. Not this "BOOMBAYAH" or "Lalisa" but this girl, Lisa changed it all. Lisa done really big in my life. Lisa took me out if my shell, Lisa took me out of my messy head, Lisa saved me from myself. I used to be alone, I used to overreact, overthink, I easily get irritated and mad, I'm the type who hates the world. But maaan Lisa made me realize how beautiful life can be. How beautiful the world it is. Her story become my inspiration, Lisa itself became my calm, my motivation my core. Suddenly I became "oh man chill that's okay" "dude everything's gonna be okay" that's why everytime I meet, read people who fabricated malicious stuffs about her, or hates Lisa. I feel sad and mad, because nobody knows her impact to one person like me. They were hurting her, while Lisa itself don't realize that she saves people like me. And that's the only truth. I know.
